obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (12164)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789&sectionId=12164&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Prohibition of`
  line `Employment as Manual Scavengersand their Rehabilitation Act, 2013.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^1***.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^3`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notificationin the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint:`
  line
  line `Provided that the date so notified shall not be earlier than sixty days after the date ofpublication of`
  line `^2[the said notification] in the Official Gazette`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and the Fifth Schedule`
  line `(w.e.f. 31-10-2019).`
  line
  line `2. 6th December, 2013, vide notification No.S.O. 2989(E), dated 1st October, 2013, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary,`
  line `Part II, Sec. 3(ii).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 17 of 2015, s.3 and the Second Schedule, for "the notification" (w.e.f. 13-5-2015).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (12165)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789&sectionId=12165&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,—`
  line
  line `(a) "agency" means any agency, other than a local authority, which mayundertake sanitation`
  line `facilities in an area and includes a contractor or a firm or a companywhich engages in development`
  line `and maintenance of real estate;`
  line
  line `(b) "appropriate government", in relation to Cantonment Boards, railway lands,and lands and`
  line `buildings owned by the Central Government, a Central Public SectorUndertaking or an autonomous`
  line `body wholly or substantially funded by the CentralGovernment, means the Central Government and`
  line `in all other cases, the StateGovernment;`
  line
  line `(c) "Chief Executive Officer", in relation to a Municipality or Panchayat, means,its senior-most`
  line `executive officer, by whatever name called;`
  line
  line `(d) "hazardous cleaning" by an employee, in relation to a sewer or septic tank,means its manual`
  line `cleaning by such employee without the employer fulfilling hisobligations to provide protective gear`
  line `and other cleaning devices and ensuringobservance of safety precautions, as may be prescribed or`
  line `provided in any other law,for the time being in force or rules made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(e) "insanitary latrine" means a latrine which requires human excreta to be cleanedor otherwise`
  line `handled manually, either in situ, or in an open drain or pit into which theexcreta is discharged or`
  line `flushed out, before the excreta fully decomposes in suchmanner as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that a water flush latrine in a railway passenger coach, when cleanedby an employee`
  line `with the help of such devices and using such protective gear, as theCentral Government may notify in`
  line `this behalf, shall not be deemed to be an insanitary latrine.`
  line
  line `(f) "local authority" means,—`
  line
  line `(i) a Municipality or a Panchayat, as defined in clause (e) and clause (f) ofarticle 243P of the`
  line `Constitution, which is responsible for sanitation in its area ofjurisdiction;`
  line
  line `(ii) a Cantonment Board constituted under section 10 of the CantonmentsAct, 2006`
  line `(41 of 2006); and`
  line
  line `(iii) a railway authority;`
  line
  line `(g) "manual scavenger" means a person engaged or employed, at thecommencement of this Act`
  line `or at any time thereafter, by an individual or a local authorityor an agency or a contractor, for`
  line `manually cleaning, carrying, disposing of, or otherwisehandling in any manner, human excreta in an`
  line `insanitary latrine or in an open drain or pitinto which the human excreta from the insanitary latrines is`
  line `disposed of, or on arailway track or in such other spaces or premises, as the Central Government or a`
  line `StateGovernment may notify, before the excreta fully decomposes in such manner as may`
  line `beprescribed, and the expression manual scavenging shall be construed accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purpose of this clause,—`
  line
  line `(a) "engaged or employed" means being engaged or employed on a regularor contract`
  line basis;
  line
  line `(b) a person engaged or employed to clean excreta with the help of suchdevices and using`
  line `such protective gear, as the Central Government may notifyin this behalf, shall not be deemed`
  line `to be a 'manual scavenger';`
  line
  line `(h) "National Commission for Safai Karmacharis" means the National Commissionfor Safai`
  line `Karamcharis constituted under section 3 of the National Commission for SafaiKarmacharis Act,`
  line `1993(64 of 1993) and continued by Resolution of the Government of India in theMinistry of Social`
  line `Justice and Empowerment vide No.17015/18/2003-SCD-VI, dated24th February, 2004 and as`
  line `amended from time to time;`
  line
  line `(i) “notification” means a notification published in the Official Gazette and theexpression`
  line `“notify” shall be construed accordingly;`
  line
  line `(j) “occupier”, in relation to the premises where an insanitary latrine exists, orsomeone is`
  line `employed as a manual scavenger, means the person who, for the timebeing, is in occupation of such`
  line premises;
  line
  line `(k) “owner”, in relation to the premises where an insanitary latrine exists orsomeone is employed`
  line `as a manual scavenger, means, the person who, for the timebeing has legal title to such premises;`
  line
  line `(l) “prescribed” means prescribed by the rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(m) “railway authority” means an authority administering railway land, as maybe notified by the`
  line `Central Government in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(n) “railway land” shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause (32A) ofsection 2 of the`
  line `Railways Act, 1989 (24 of 1989);`
  line
  line `(o) “sanitary latrine” means a latrine which is not an „insanitary latrine‟;`
  line
  line `(p) “septic tank” means a water-tight settling tank or chamber, normally locatedunderground,`
  line `which is used to receive and hold human excreta, allowing it to decomposethrough bacterial activity;`
  line
  line `(q) “sewer” means an underground conduit or pipe for carrying off human excreta,besides other`
  line `waste matter and drainage wastes;`
  line
  line `(r) “State Government”, in relation to a Union territory, means the Administratorthereof`
  line `appointed under article 239 of the Constitution;`
  line
  line `(s) “survey” means a survey of manual scavengers undertaken in pursuance ofsection 11 or`
  line `section 14.`
  line
  line `(2) Words and expressions used and not defined in this Act, but defined in theCantonments Act, 2006`
  line `(41 of 2006), shall have the same meanings respectively assigned to them in thatAct.`
  line
  line `(3) The reference to a Municipality under Chapters IV to VIII of this Act shall includea reference to,`
  line `as the case may be, the Cantonment Board or the railway authority, in respectof areas included within the`
  line `jurisdiction of the Cantonment Board and the railway land,respectively.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (12166)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Act to have overriding effect.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789&sectionId=12166&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall have effect notwithstanding`
  line `anything inconsistenttherewith contained in the Employment of Manual Scavengers and Construction of`
  line `DryLatrines (Prohibition) Act, 1993 ( 46 of 1993) or in any other law, or in any instrument having effect`
  line `byvirtue of any other law.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (12167)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Local authorities to survey insanitary latrines and provide sanitary community latrines.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789&sectionId=12167&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `Every local authority shall,—`
  line
  line `(a) carry out a survey of insanitary latrines existing within its jurisdiction, andpublish a list of`
  line `such insanitary latrines, in such manner as may be prescribed, withina period of two months from the`
  line `date of commencement of this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) give a notice to the occupier, within fifteen days from the date of publicationof the list under`
  line `clause (a), to either demolish the insanitary latrine or convert it into asanitary latrine, within a period`
  line `of six months from the date of commencement of thisAct:`
  line
  line `Provided that the local authority may for sufficient reasons to be recorded inwriting extend the`
  line `said period not exceeding three months;`
  line
  line `(c) construct, within a period not exceeding nine months from the date ofcommencement of this`
  line `Act, such number of sanitary community latrines as it considersnecessary, in the areas where`
  line `insanitary latrines have been found.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions contained in sub-section (1), Municipalities,Cantonment`
  line `Boards and railway authorities shall also construct adequate number of sanitarycommunity latrines,`
  line `within such period not exceeding three years from the date ofcommencement of this Act, as the`
  line `appropriate Government may, by notification, specify, soas to eliminate the practice of open defecation`
  line `in their jurisdiction.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall be the responsibility of local authorities to construct community sanitarylatrines as`
  line `specified in sub-sections (1) and (2), and also to make arrangements for theirhygienic upkeep at all`
  line times.
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this section, “community” in relation to railwayauthorities means`
  line `passengers, staff and other authorised users of railways.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (12168)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Prohibition of insanitary latrines and employment and engagement of manual scavenger.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789&sectionId=12168&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `Notwithstanding anything inconsistent therewith contained in the Employmentof Manual Scavengers and`
  line `Construction of Dry Latrines (Prohibition) Act, 1993 (46 of 1993), no person,local authority or any`
  line `agency shall, after the date of commencement of this Act,—`
  line
  line `(a) construct an insanitary latrine; or`
  line
  line `(b) engage or employ, either directly or indirectly, a manual scavenger, and everyperson so`
  line `engaged or employed shall stand discharged immediately from any obligation,express or implied, to`
  line `do manual scavenging.`
  line
  line `(2) Every insanitary latrine existing on the date of commencement of this Act, shalleither be`
  line `demolished or be converted into a sanitary latrine, by the occupier at his own cost,before the expiry of`
  line `the period so specified in clause (b) of sub-section (1) of section 4:`
  line
  line `Provided that where there are several occupiers in relation to an insanitary latrine, theliability to`
  line `demolish or convert it shall lie with,—`
  line
  line `(a) the owner of the premises, in case one of the occupiers happens to be theowner; and`
  line
  line `(b) all the occupiers, jointly and severally, in all other cases:`
  line
  line `Provided that the State Government may give assistance for conversion of insanitarylatrines into`
  line `sanitary latrines to occupiers from such categories of persons and on suchscale, as it may, by notification,`
  line `specify:`
  line
  line `Provided further that non-receipt of State assistance shall not be a valid ground tomaintain or use an`
  line `insanitary latrine, beyond the said period of nine months.`
  line
  line `(3) If any occupier fails to demolish an insanitary latrine or convert it into a sanitarylatrine within the`
  line `period specified in sub-section (2), the local authority having jurisdictionover the area in which such`
  line `insanitary latrine is situated, shall, after giving notice of not lessthan twenty one days to the occupier,`
  line `either convert such latrine into a sanitary latrine, ordemolish such insanitary latrine, and shall be entitled`
  line `to recover the cost of such conversionor, as the case may be, of demolition, from such occupier in such`
  line `manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (12169)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Contract, agreement, etc., to be void.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789&sectionId=12169&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any contract, agreement or other instrument entered`
  line `into or executed before thedate of commencement of this Act, engaging or employing a person for the`
  line `purpose ofmanual scavenging shall, on the date of commencement of this Act, be terminated and`
  line `suchcontract, agreement or other instrument shall be void and inoperative and no compensationshall be`
  line `payable therefor.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), no person employed orengaged as a`
  line `manual scavenger on a full-time basis shall be retrenched by his employer, butshall be retained, subject to`
  line `his willingness, in employment on at least the same emoluments,and shall be assigned work other than`
  line `manual scavenging.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (12170)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Prohibition of persons from engagement or employment for hazardous cleaning of sewers and septic tanks.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789&sectionId=12170&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `No person, local authority or any agency shall, from such date as the StateGovernment`
  line `may notify, which shall not be later than one year from the date of commencementof this Act, engage or`
  line `employ, either directly or indirectly, any person for hazardous cleaningof a sewer or a septic tank.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (12171)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Penalty for contravention of section 5 or section 6.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789&sectionId=12171&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `Whoever contravenes the provisions of`
  line `section 5 or section 6 shall for the firstcontravention be punishable with imprisonment for a term which`
  line `may extend to one year orwith fine which may extend to fifty thousand rupees or with both, and for anysubsequentcontravention with imprisonment which may extend to two years or with fine which`
  line `mayextend to one lakh rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (12172)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Penalty for contravention of section 7.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789&sectionId=12172&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `Whoever contravenes the provisions of section 7 shall`
  line `for the first contravention bepunishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years or`
  line `with fine whichmay extend to two lakh rupees or with both, and for any subsequent contravention`
  line `withimprisonment which may extend to five years or with fine which may extend to five lakhrupees, or`
  line `with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (12173)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Limitation of prosecution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789&sectionId=12173&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `No court shall take cognizance of any offence punishable under this`
  line `Actexceptupon a complaint thereof is made by a person in this behalf within three months from the dateof`
  line `the occurrence of the alleged commission of the offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (12174)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Survey of manual scavengers in urban areas by Municipalities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789&sectionId=12174&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any Municipality has`
  line `reason to believe that some persons are engaged oremployed in manual scavenging within its jurisdiction,`
  line `the Chief Executive Officer of suchMunicipality shall cause a survey to be undertaken to identify such`
  line persons.
  line
  line `(2) The content and methodology of the survey referred to in sub-section (1) shall besuch as may be`
  line `prescribed, and it shall be completed within a period of two months from itscommencement in the case of`
  line `Municipal Corporations, and within a period of one month inthe case of other Municipalities.`
  line
  line `(3) The Chief Executive Officer of the Municipality, in whose jurisdiction the survey isundertaken,`
  line `shall be responsible for accurate and timely completion of the survey.`
  line
  line `(4) After completion of the survey, the Chief Executive Officer shall cause to be drawnup a`
  line `provisional list of persons found to be working as manual scavengers within thejurisdiction of his`
  line `Municipality and fulfilling the eligibility conditions as may be prescribed,shall cause such provisional list`
  line `to be published for general information in such manner, asmay be prescribed, and shall invite objections`
  line `to the list from the general public.`
  line
  line `(5) Any person having any objection, either to the inclusion or exclusion of any namein the`
  line `provisional list published in pursuance of sub-section (4), shall, within a period offifteen days from such`
  line `publication, file an objection, in such form as the Municipality maynotify, to the Chief Executive Officer.`
  line
  line `(6) All objections received in pursuance of sub-section (5), shall be enquired into, andthereafter a`
  line `final list of persons found to be working as manual scavengers within the locallimits of the municipality,`
  line `shall be published by it in such manner, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(7) As soon as the final list of manual scavengers, referred to in sub-section (6) ispublished, the`
  line `persons included in the said list shall, subject to the provisions ofsub-section (2) of section 6, stand`
  line `discharged from any obligation to work as manual scavengers.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (12175)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Application by an urban manual scavenger for identification.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789&sectionId=12175&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person working as a`
  line `manual scavenger in an urban area, may, either duringthe survey undertaken by the Municipality in`
  line `pursuance of section 11, within whosejurisdiction he works, or at any time thereafter, apply, in such`
  line `manner, as may be prescribed,to the Chief Executive Officer of the Municipality, or to any other officer`
  line `authorised by him inthis behalf, for being identified as a manual scavenger.`
  line
  line `(2) On receipt of an application under sub-section (1), the Chief Executive Officer shallcause it to be`
  line `enquired into, either as part of the survey undertaken under section 11, or,when no such survey is in`
  line `progress, within fifteen days of receipt of such application, toascertain whether the applicant is a manual`
  line scavenger.
  line
  line `(3) If an application is received under sub-section (1) when a survey under section 11is not in`
  line `progress, and is found to be true after enquiry in accordance with sub-section (2),action shall be taken to add the name of such a person to the final list published undersub-section (6) of section 11, and the`
  line `consequences mentioned in sub-section (7) thereofshall follow`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (12176)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Rehabilitation of persons identified as manual scavengers by a Municipality.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789&sectionId=12176&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person`
  line `included in the final list of manual scavengers published in pursuanceof sub-section (6) of section 11 or`
  line `added thereto in pursuance of sub-section (3) of section 12,shall be rehabilitated in the following manner,`
  line `namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) he shall be given, within one month,—`
  line
  line `(i) a photo identity card, containing, inter alia, details of all members ofhis family dependent`
  line `on him, and`
  line
  line `(ii) such initial, one time, cash assistance, as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(b) his children shall be entitled to scholarship as per the relevant scheme of theCentral`
  line `Government or the State Government or the local authorities, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(c) he shall be allotted a residential plot and financial assistance for houseconstruction, or a readybuilt`
  line `house, with financial assistance, subject to eligibilityand willingness of the manual scavenger,`
  line `and the provisions of the relevant scheme ofthe Central Government or the State Government or the`
  line `concerned local authority;`
  line
  line `(d) he, or at least one adult member of his family, shall be given, subject toeligibility and`
  line `willingness, training in a livelihood skill, and shall be paid a monthlystipend of not less than three`
  line `thousand rupees, during the period of such training;`
  line
  line `(e) he, or at least one adult member of his family, shall be given, subject toeligibility and`
  line `willingness, subsidy and concessional loan for taking up an alternativeoccupation on a sustainable`
  line `basis, in such manner as may be stipulated in the relevantscheme of the Central Government or the`
  line `State Government or the concerned localauthority;`
  line
  line `(f) he shall be provided such other legal and programmatic assistance, as theCentral Government`
  line `or State Government may notify in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) The District Magistrate of the district concerned shall be responsible forrehabilitation of each`
  line `manual scavenger in accordance with the provisions of sub-section (1)and the State Government or the`
  line `District Magistrate concerned may, in addition, assignresponsibilities in his behalf to officers subordinate`
  line `to the District Magistrate and to officersof the concerned Municipality.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (12177)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Survey of manual scavengers in rural areas by Panchayats.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789&sectionId=12177&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `If any Panchayat has reason to`
  line `believe that some persons are engaged in manualscavenging within its jurisdiction, the Chief Executive`
  line `Officer of suchPanchayat shall causea survey of such manual scavengers to be undertaken, mutatis`
  line `mutandis, in accordance withthe provisions of section 11 and section 12, to identify such person.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (12178)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Application by a rural manual scavenger for identification.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789&sectionId=12178&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person working as a`
  line `manual scavenger, in a rural area, may, either duringthe survey undertaken by the Panchayat within`
  line `whose jurisdiction he works, in pursuance ofsection 14 or at any time thereafter, apply, in such manner, as`
  line `may be prescribed, to the ChiefExecutive Officer of the concerned Panchayat, or to any other officer`
  line `authorised by him inthis behalf, for being identified as a manual scavenger.`
  line
  line `(2) On receipt of an application under sub-section (1), the Chief Executive Officer shallcause it to be`
  line `enquired into, either as part of the survey undertaken under section 14 or whenno such survey is in`
  line `progress, within fifteen days of receipt of such application, so as toascertain whether the applicant is a`
  line `manual scavenger.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (12179)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Rehabilitation of persons identified as manual scavengers by a Panchayat.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789&sectionId=12179&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `Any person`
  line `included in the final list of manual scavengers, published in pursuanceof section 14 or added thereto in`
  line `pursuance of sub-section (2) of section 15 shall berehabilitated, mutatis mutandis, in the manner laid`
  line `down for urban manual scavengers insection 13.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (12180)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Responsibility of local authorities to ensure elimination of insanitary latrines.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789&sectionId=12180&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, itshall be the`
  line `responsibility of every local authority to ensure, through awareness campaignor in such other manner that`
  line `after the expiry of a period of nine months, from the date ofcommencement of this Act,—`
  line
  line `(i) no insanitary latrine is constructed, maintained or used within its jurisdiction;`
  line and
  line
  line `(ii) in case of contravention of clause (i), action is taken against the occupierunder`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 5.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (12181)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Authorities who may be specified for implementing provisions of this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789&sectionId=12181&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `The appropriate`
  line `Government may confer such powers and impose such duties onlocal authority and District Magistrate as`
  line `may be necessary to ensure that the provisions ofthis Act are properly carried out, and a local authority`
  line `and the District Magistrate may,specify the subordinate officers, who shall exercise all or any of the`
  line `powers, and perform allor any of the duties, so conferred or imposed, and the local limits within which`
  line `such powersor duties shall be carried out by the officer or officers so specified.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (12182)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Duty of District Magistrate and authorised officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789&sectionId=12182&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `The District Magistrate and the authority`
  line `authorised under section 18 or any othersubordinate officers specified by them under that section shall`
  line `ensure that, after the expiryof such period as specified for the purpose of this Act,—`
  line
  line `(a) no person is engaged or employed as manual scavenger within theirjurisdiction;`
  line
  line `(b) no one constructs, maintains, uses or makes available for use, an insanitarylatrine;`
  line
  line `(c) manual scavengers identified under this Act are rehabilitated in accordancewith section 13, or`
  line `as the case may be, section 16;`
  line
  line `(d) persons contravening the provisions of section 5 or section 6 or section 7are investigated and`
  line `prosecuted under the provisions of this Act; and`
  line
  line `(e) all provisions of this Act applicable within his jurisdiction are duly compliedwith.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (12183)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Appointment of inspectors and their powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789&sectionId=12183&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) The appropriate Government may, by`
  line `notification, appoint such persons as itthinks fit to be inspectors for the purposes of this Act, and define`
  line `the local limits withinwhich they shall exercise their powers under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to any rules made in this behalf, an inspector may, within the local limits ofhis`
  line `jurisdiction, enter, at all reasonable times, with such assistance as he considers necessary,any premises or`
  line `place for the purpose of,—`
  line
  line `(a) examining and testing any latrine, open drain or pit or for conducting aninspection of any`
  line `premises or place, where he has reason to believe that an offenceunder this Act has been or is being or`
  line `is about to be committed, and to preventemployment of any person as manual scavenger;`
  line
  line `(b) examine any person whom he finds in such premises or place and who, he hasreasonable`
  line `cause to believe, is employed as a manual scavenger therein, or is otherwisein a position to furnish`
  line `information about compliance or non-compliance with theprovisions of this Act and the rules made`
  line thereunder;
  line
  line `(c) require any person whom he finds on such premises, to give informationwhich is in his power`
  line `to give, with respect to the names and addresses of personsemployed on such premises as manual`
  line `scavenger and of the persons or agency orcontractor employing or engaging them;`
  line
  line `(d) seize or take copies of such registers, record of wages or notices or portionsthereof as he may`
  line `consider relevant in respect of an offence under this Act which hehas reason to believe has been`
  line `committed by the principal employer or agency; and`
  line
  line `(e) exercise such other powers as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Any person required to produce any document or thing or to give any informationrequired by an`
  line `inspector under sub-section (2) shall be deemed to be legally bound to do sowithin the meaning of`
  line `section 175 and section 176 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
  line
  line `(4) The provisions of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), shall, so far as may be,apply`
  line `to any such search or seizure under sub-section (2) as they apply to such search orseizure made under the`
  line `authority of a warrant issued under section 94 of the said Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (12184)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Offences to be tried by Executive Magistrate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789&sectionId=12184&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may confer, on an`
  line `Executive Magistrate, the powers of aJudicial Magistrate of the first class for the trial of offences under`
  line `this Act; and, on suchconferment of powers, the Executive Magistrate, on whom the powers are so`
  line `conferred, shallbe deemed, for the purposes of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), to be a`
  line `Judicial Magistrateof the first class.`
  line
  line `(2) An offence under this Act may be tried summarily.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (12185)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Offence to be cognizable and non-bailable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789&sectionId=12185&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of`
  line `Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974),every offence under this Act shall be cognizable and non-bailable.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (12186)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789&sectionId=12186&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence under this Act has been committed by a`
  line `company, everyperson who, at the time the offence was committed, was in charge of, and was responsible`
  line `to,the company for the conduct of the business of the company, as well as the company, shallbe deemed`
  line `to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against andpunished accordingly.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where any offence underthis Act has been`
  line `committed by a company and it is proved that offence has been committedwith the consent or connivance`
  line `of, or is attributable to, any neglect on the part of, anydirector, manager, secretary or other officer of the`
  line `company, such director, manager, secretaryor other officer shall be deemed to be guilty of that offence`
  line `and shall be liable to be proceededagainst and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this section,—`
  line
  line `(a) “company” means any body corporate and includes a firm or other associationof individuals;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) “director”, in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (12187)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Vigilance Committees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789&sectionId=12187&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every State Government shall, by notification, constitute a Vigilance`
  line `Committeefor each district and each Sub-Division.`
  line
  line `(2) Each Vigilance Committee constituted for a district shall consist of the followingmembers,`
  line `namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the District Magistrate—Chairperson, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(b) all members of the State Legislature belonging to the Scheduled Casteselected from the`
  line `district—members:`
  line
  line `Provided that if a district has no member of the State Legislature belonging tothe Scheduled`
  line `Castes, the State Government may nominate such number of othermembers of the State Legislature`
  line `from the district, not exceeding two, as it may deemappropriate.`
  line
  line `(c) the district Superintendent of Police— member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(d) the Chief Executive Officer of,—`
  line
  line `(i) the Panchayat at the district level—member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(ii) the Municipality of the district headquarters—member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(iii) any other Municipal Corporation constituted in the district—member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(iv) Cantonment Board, if any, situated in the district—member,ex officio;`
  line
  line `(e) one representative be nominated by the railway authority located in thedistrict;`
  line
  line `(f) not more than four social workers belonging to organisation working for theprohibition of`
  line `manual scavenging and rehabilitation of manual scavengers, or,representing the scavenger`
  line `community, resident in the district, to be nominated by theDistrict Magistrate, two of whom shall be`
  line women;
  line
  line `(g) one person to represent the financial and credit institutions in the district, tobe nominated by`
  line `the District Magistrate;`
  line
  line `(h) the district-level officer in-charge of the Scheduled Castes Welfare—Member-Secretary,`
  line `ex officio;`
  line
  line `(i) district-level officers of Departments and agencies who, in the opinion of theDistrict`
  line `Magistrate, subject to general orders, if any, of the State Government, have asignificant role to play in`
  line `the implementation of this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) Each Vigilance Committee, constituted for a Sub-Division, shall consist of thefollowing members,`
  line `namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the Sub-Divisional Magistrate—Chairperson, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(b) the Chairpersons and the Chief Executive Officers of Panchayats atintermediate level of the`
  line `Sub-Division, and where Panchayats at intermediate level, donot exist, Chairpersons from two`
  line `Panchayats at Village level to be nominated by theSub-Divisional Magistrate—member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(c) the Sub-Divisional Officer of Police—member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(d) Chief Executive Officer of—`
  line
  line `(i) the Municipality of the Sub-Divisional headquarters—member,ex officio; and`
  line
  line `(ii) Cantonment Board, if any, situated in the Sub-Division—member,ex officio;`
  line
  line `(e) one representative to be nominated by the railway authority located in the`
  line `Sub-Division—member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(f) two social workers belonging to the organisation working for the prohibitionof manual`
  line `scavenging and rehabilitation of the manual scavengers, or representing thescavenger community`
  line `resident in the Sub-Division, to be nominated by the DistrictMagistrate, one of whom shall be a`
  line woman;
  line
  line `(g) one person to represent the financial and credit institutions in theSub-Division, to be`
  line `nominated by the Sub-Divisional Magistrate;`
  line
  line `(h) the Sub-Divisional level officer in-charge of Scheduled Castes welfare—Member-Secretary,`
  line `ex officio;`
  line
  line `(i) Sub-Divisional level officers of Department and agencies who in the opinionof the`
  line `Sub-Divisional Magistrate, subject to any general orders of the State Governmentor the District`
  line `Magistrate, have a significant role to play in the implementation of thisActmember, ex officio.`
  line
  line `(4) Each Vigilance Committee constituted at district and Sub-Divisional level shallmeet at least once`
  line `in every three months.`
  line
  line `(5) No proceeding of a Vigilance Committees shall be invalid merely by reason of anydefect in its`
  line constitution.
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (12188)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Functions of Vigilance Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789&sectionId=12188&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `The functions of Vigilance Committee shall be—`
  line
  line `(a) to advise the District Magistrate or, as the case may be, the Sub-DivisionalMagistrate, on the`
  line `action which needs to be taken, to ensure that the provisions of thisAct or of any rule made thereunder`
  line `are properly implemented;`
  line
  line `(b) to oversee the economic and social rehabilitation of manual scavengers;`
  line
  line `(c) to co-ordinate the functions of all concerned agencies with a view to channelise adequate`
  line `credit for the rehabilitation of manual scavengers;`
  line
  line `(d) to monitor the registration of offences under this Act and their investigationand prosecution`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (12189)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `State Monitoring Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789&sectionId=12189&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every State Government shall, by notification, constitute a`
  line `State MonitoringCommittee, consisting of the following members, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the Chief Minister of State or a Minister nominated by him—Chairperson,ex officio;`
  line
  line `(b) the Minister-in-charge of the Scheduled Castes Welfare, and such otherDepartment, as the`
  line `State Government may notify;`
  line
  line `(c) Chairperson of the State Commissions for Safai Karamcharis, and ScheduledCastes, if any—`
  line `member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(d) representatives of the National Commission for Scheduled Castes, and SafaiKaramcharis—`
  line `member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(e) not less than two members of the State Legislature belonging to the ScheduledCastes,`
  line `nominated by the State Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that if any State Legislature has no member belonging to theScheduled Castes, the State`
  line `Government may nominate the members belonging to theScheduled Tribes;`
  line
  line `(f) the Director-General of Police— member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(g) Secretaries to the State Government in the Departments of Home, PanchayatiRaj, Urban Local`
  line `Bodies, and such other Departments, as the State Government may notify;`
  line
  line `(h) Chief Executive Officer of at least one Municipal Corporation, Panchayat atthe district-level,`
  line `Cantonment Board and railway authority as the State Governmentmay notify;`
  line
  line `(i) not more than four social workers belonging to organisation working for theprohibition of`
  line `manual scavenging and rehabilitation of manual scavengers, or,representing the scavenger`
  line `community, resident in the State, to be nominated by theState Government, two of whom shall be`
  line women;
  line
  line `(j) State-level head of the convener Bank of the State Level Bankers Committee—member,`
  line `ex officio;`
  line
  line `(k) Secretary of the Department of the State Government dealing withdevelopment of the`
  line `Scheduled Castes—Member-Secretary, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(l) such other representative of Departments of the State Government and suchother agencies`
  line `which, in the opinion of the State Government, are concerned with theimplementation of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Monitoring Committee shall meet at least once in every six months andshall observe`
  line `such rules of procedure in regard to the transaction of business at its meetingsas may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (12190)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Functions of the State Monitoring Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789&sectionId=12190&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `The functions of the State Monitoring`
  line `Committee shall be—`
  line
  line `(a) to monitor and advise the State Government and local authorities for effectiveimplementation`
  line `of this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) to co-ordinate the functions of all concerned agencies;`
  line
  line `(c) to look into any other matter incidental thereto or connected therewith forimplementation of`
  line `this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (12191)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Duty of States or Union territories to send periodic reports to the Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789&sectionId=12191&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `Every State or Union territory Government and Union territory administration shallsend such periodic`
  line `reports to the Central Government about progress of implementation ofthis Act, as the Central`
  line `Government may require.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (12192)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Central Monitoring Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789&sectionId=12192&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, by notification, constitute a`
  line `Central MonitoringCommittee in accordance with the provisions of this section.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Monitoring Committee shall consist of the following members,namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) The Union Minister for Social Justice and Empowerment—Chairperson,ex officio;`
  line
  line `(b) Chairperson of the National Commission for Scheduled Castes—member,ex officio;`
  line
  line `(c) Minister of State in the Ministry of Social Justice and Empowerment—member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(d) Chairperson, National Commission for Safai Karamcharis—member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(e) the Member of the Planning Commission dealing with development of theScheduled Castes—`
  line `member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(f) three elected members of Parliament belonging to Scheduled Castes, two fromthe Lok Sabha`
  line `and one from the Rajya Sabha;`
  line
  line `(g) Secretaries of the Ministries of,—`
  line
  line `(i) Social Justice and Empowerment, Department of Social Justice andEmpowerment;`
  line
  line `(ii) Urban Development;`
  line
  line `(iii) Housing and Urban Poverty Alleviation;`
  line
  line `(iv) Drinking Water and Sanitation;`
  line
  line `(v) Panchayati Raj;`
  line
  line `(vi) Finance, Department of Financial Services; and`
  line
  line `(vii) Defence,`
  line
  line `members, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(h) Chairman, Railway Board—member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(i) Director-General, Defence Estates—member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(j) representatives of not less than six State Governments and one Union territory,as the`
  line `Central Government may, notify;`
  line
  line `(k) not more than six social workers belonging to organisation working for theprohibition of`
  line `manual scavenging and rehabilitation of manual scavengers, or,representing the scavenger`
  line `community, resident in the country, to be nominated bythe Chairperson, two of whom shall be`
  line women;
  line
  line `(l) Joint Secretary, Department of Social Justice and Empowerment in theMinistry of Social`
  line `Justice and Empowerment, looking after development of ScheduledCastes—Member-Secretary,`
  line `ex officio;`
  line
  line `(m) such other representatives of Central Ministries or Departments and agencieswhich, in the`
  line `opinion of the Chairperson, are concerned with the implementation ofthis Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Monitoring Committee shall meet at least once in every six months.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (12193)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Functions of the Central Monitoring Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789&sectionId=12193&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `The functions of the Central Monitoring`
  line `Committee shall be,—`
  line
  line `(a) to monitor and advise the Central Government and State Government foreffective`
  line `implementation of this Act and related laws and programmes;`
  line
  line `(b) to co-ordinate the functions of all concerned agencies;`
  line
  line `(c) to look into any other matter incidental to or connected with implementationof this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (12194)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Functions of National Commission for Safai Karamcharis.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789&sectionId=12194&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) The National Commission for`
  line `Safai Karamcharis shall perform the followingfunctions, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) to monitor the implementation of this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) to enquire into complaints regarding contravention of the provisions of thisAct, and to convey`
  line `its findings to the concerned authorities with recommendationsrequiring further action; and`
  line
  line `(c) to advise the Central and the State Governments for effective implementationof the provisions`
  line `of this Act.`
  line
  line `(d) to take suo motu notice of matter relating to non-implementation of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In the discharge of its functions under sub-section (1), the National Commissionshall have the`
  line `power to call for information with respect to any matter specified in that sub-sectionfrom any`
  line `Government or local or other authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (12195)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Power of State Government to designate an appropriate authority to monitor the implementation of this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789&sectionId=12195&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, by notification, designate a State`
  line `Commission forSafai Karamcharis or a State Commission for the Scheduled Castes or such other`
  line `statutory orother authority, as it deems fit, to perform, within the State, mutatis mutandis, the`
  line `functionsspecified in sub-section (1) of section 31.`
  line
  line `(2) An authority designated under sub-section (1) shall, within the State, have,mutatis mutandis, the`
  line `powers of the National Commission for Safai Karamcharis as specifiedin sub-section (2) of section 31.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (12196)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Duty of local authorities and other agencies to use modern technology for cleaning of sewers, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789&sectionId=12196&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall be the duty of every local authority and other agency to use`
  line `appropriatetechnological appliances for cleaning of sewers, septic tanks and other spaces within`
  line `theircontrol with a view to eliminating the need for the manual handling of excreta in the processof their`
  line cleaning.
  line
  line `(2) It shall be the duty of the appropriate Government to promote, through financialassistance,`
  line `incentives and otherwise, the use of modern technology, as mentioned in sub-section(1).`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (12197)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789&sectionId=12197&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against an appropriateGovernment or any officer of the appropriate Government or any member of the`
  line `Committeefor anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (12198)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Jurisdiction of civil courts barred.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789&sectionId=12198&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `No civil court shall have jurisdiction in respect of any`
  line `matter to which any provisionof this Act applies and no injunction shall be granted by any civil court in`
  line `respect of anything,which is done or intended to be done, by or under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (12199)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Power of appropriate Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789&sectionId=12199&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) The appropriate Government shall, by`
  line `notification, make rules for carrying outthe provisions of this Act, within a period not exceeding three`
  line `months from the date ofcommencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, suchrules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the obligation of an employer, under clause (d) of sub-section (1) ofsection 2;`
  line
  line `(b) the manner in which the excreta fully decomposes under clauses (e) and (g)of sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 2;`
  line
  line `(c) the manner of carrying out survey of insanitary latrine and publishing listthereof under`
  line `clause (a) of sub-section (1) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(d) procedure of giving notice and recovering cost of demolition of an insanitarylatrine undersubsection`
  line `(3) of section 5;`
  line
  line `(e) content and methodology of the survey under sub-section (2) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(f) the eligibility conditions for identification of manual scavengers and publicationof provisional`
  line `list of persons found to be working as manual scavengers under sub-section(4) of`
  line `section 11;`
  line
  line `(g) publication of final list of persons found to be working as manual scavengersunder subsection`
  line `(6) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(h) manner of application to be made to the Chief Executive Officer of themunicipality, or to an`
  line `officer authorised by him in this behalf, under sub-section (1) ofsection 12 or, as the case may be,`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 15;`
  line
  line `(i) provision of initial, one time, cash assistance under sub-clause (ii) of clause(a) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 13;`
  line
  line `(j) such other powers of Inspectors under clause (e) of sub-section (2) of section20; and`
  line
  line `(k) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made under this Act by the Central Government shall be laid, as soon as maybe after it`
  line `is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirtydays which may`
  line `be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, beforethe expiry of the session`
  line `immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid,both Houses agree in making any`
  line `modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the ruleshould not be made, the rule shall thereafter`
  line `have effect only in such modified form or be of noeffect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such`
  line `modification or annulment shall be withoutprejudice to the validity of anything previously done under`
  line `that rule.`
  line
  line `(4) Every rule made under this Act by the State Government shall, as soon as may beafter it is made,`
  line `be laid before each House of State Legislature, where there are two Housesand where there is one House`
  line `of State Legislature, before that House.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (12200)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Power of Central Government to make model rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789&sectionId=12200&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained`
  line `in section 36 of this Act:—`
  line
  line `(a) the Central Government shall, by notification, publish model rules for theguidance and use of`
  line `State Governments; and`
  line
  line `(b) in case the State Government fails to notify the rules under section 36 of thisAct within the`
  line `period of three months specified therein, then the model rules as notifiedby the Central Government`
  line `shall be deemed to have come into effect, mutatis mutandis,in such State, till such time as the State`
  line `Government notifies its rules.`
  line
  line `(2) The model rules made by the Central Government under this Act shall be laid, assoon as may be`
  line `after they are made, before each House of Parliament while it is in session, fora total period of thirty days`
  line `which may be comprised in one session or in two or moresuccessive sessions, and if, before the expiry of`
  line `the session immediately following thesession or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses make any`
  line `modification in therule, the rule shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form; so, however, that`
  line `anysuch modification shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously doneunder that`
  line rule.
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (12201)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789&sectionId=12201&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of this`
  line `Act, the CentralGovernment may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions, notinconsistent with the provisions of this Act, as may appear to it to be necessary or expedientfor the`
  line `removal of the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made in relation to a State after the expiration ofthree years from`
  line `thecommencement of this Act in that State.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall, as soon as may be after it is made, be laidbefore each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (12202)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Power to exempt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789&sectionId=12202&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00008_201325_1517807327789
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `(1) The appropriate Government may, by a general or special order published`
  line `in theOfficial Gazette, for reasons to be recorded, and subject to such conditions as it may impose,exempt`
  line `any area, category of buildings or class of persons from any provisions of this Act orfrom any specified`
  line `requirement contained in this Act or any rule, order, notification, bye-lawsor scheme made thereunder or`
  line `dispense with the observance of any such requirement in aclass or classes of cases, for a period not`
  line `exceeding six months at a time.`
  line
  line `(2) Every general or special order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as maybe after it is`
  line `made, before each House of Parliament or each House of State Legislature, wherethere are two Houses`
  line `and where there is one House of State Legislature, before that House.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
